@startuml
' @id(DOM-CYCLE)
' @id(DOM-CYCLE-DIFF)
' @id(DOM-ELEMENT-DESCRIPTION)
' @id(DOM-CYCLE-REGISTRY)
'
' Objective-side domain model for cycle tracking. New concepts, absent on
' the current side until /mdd-implement + /mdd-map close the parity gap.
'
' @desc(DOM-CYCLE, "One tracked MDD loop: its entry point, description, status, the model files it touched, and its before/after snapshot directories.")
' @desc(DOM-CYCLE-DIFF, "Per-diagram element partition between a cycle's before and after current-side snapshots: unchanged, added, removed.")
' @desc(DOM-ELEMENT-DESCRIPTION, "The @desc(<ID>, text) marker: a one-line human description attached to a model @id, surfaced in the MODEL CONTEXT card.")
' @desc(DOM-CYCLE-REGISTRY, "Scans .mdd/cycles/ into an ordered list of Cycle records for the viewer rail and diff view; analogous to ModelRegistry.")
title Cycle tracking domain (objective)

enum EntryPoint {
  Generate
  Map
}

enum CycleStatus {
  Open
  Closed
  Aborted
}

class Cycle {
  + number : int
  + slug : String
  + entry : EntryPoint
  + description : String
  + status : CycleStatus
  + openedAt : Timestamp
  + closedAt : Timestamp?
  + touchedFiles : List<String>
  + beforeDir : Path
  + afterDir : Path?
}

class CycleDiff {
  + diagram : String
  + unchanged : Set<ElementKey>
  + added : Set<ElementKey>
  + removed : Set<ElementKey>
  + annotatedPuml : Path
}

class ElementDescription {
  + targetId : String
  + text : String
}

class CycleRegistry {
  + cyclesDir : Path
  + scan() : List<Cycle>
  + cycle(number) : Cycle?
  + latest() : Cycle?
}

CycleRegistry "1" o-- "*" Cycle : discovers >
Cycle "1" o-- "*" CycleDiff : closes with >
Cycle --> EntryPoint
Cycle --> CycleStatus
ElementDescription "*" ..> "1" Cycle : authored during

note bottom of ElementDescription
  targetId must resolve to an existing model
  @id on the same side. One description per
  significant element. Constrained by
  OCL-ELEMENT-DESC-NONEMPTY.
end note

note bottom of CycleDiff
  unchanged, added and removed are pairwise
  disjoint (OCL-CYCLE-DIFF-PARTITION). Element
  identity is the @id, or the stable PlantUML
  alias/label when an element has no @id.
end note

note bottom of Cycle
  A Closed cycle must have a non-null afterDir
  and at least one CycleDiff
  (OCL-CYCLE-CLOSED-HAS-SNAPSHOTS). entry is
  Generate iff the run started from a
  description (OCL-CYCLE-ENTRY-VALID).
end note
@enduml
